Simulation records, lattice tests, and verification runs.

---

interpretations/

Framework-consistent interpretations that have not yet been derived.

---

redo/

Paths that require reconstruction or re-derivation.

Failure of a derivation does not imply failure of the theory.

---

awareness/

Separate awareness-related research track.

Maintained independently from the physics audit.

---

addendum/

Research queue, discussion records, future audit candidates, and supporting notes.

---

Promotion Rules

Nothing moves into Proven Results without:

- Named derivation
- Experimental support
- Closed gate condition

Nothing moves from Candidate to Core automatically.

All changes must leave an audit trail.

---

Guiding Principle

Definitions before proofs.

Proofs before interpretations.

Interpretations before conclusions.

Preserve the source.

Do not compress the source into summaries.